CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)

CSS is used to style HTML webpages. It controls layout, colors, fonts, spacing, and design.


Types of CSS

1. Inline CSS
   Used inside HTML tag
   Example: <tag style="property: value;"></tag>

2. Internal CSS
   Written inside <head> section
   Example:

<style>
h1 {
  color: red;
}
</style>

3. External CSS
   Written in separate .css file
   Example:
   h1 {
   color: green;
   }

---

Basic Structure

selector {
property: value;
}

---

Common Properties

Font:

* font-family
* font-size
* font-style
* font-weight

Color & Background:

* color
* background-color
* background-image

Text:

* letter-spacing
* word-spacing
* text-decoration
* line-height

Box Model:

* margin
* padding
* border
* width
* height

---

Examples

Inline CSS:

<table style="width:200px; background-color:black;">
</table>

Internal CSS:

<html>
<head>
<style>
h1 {
  color: red;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Styled Heading</h1>
</body>
</html>

External CSS (mystyle.css):
h1 {
color: green;
font-size: 36px;
}

---

Summary

* CSS is used for design
* Three types: Inline, Internal, External
* External CSS is best for large projects
